# ROADMAP-100 #8 — Codeowners auto-routing per project.
#
# Reviewer agent reads this file to pick the right rubric for each diff.
# Each pattern maps to a virtual reviewer profile (handled by reviewer-daemon
# via team membership, not real users); humans only get pinged on explicit
# escalation tags below.
#
# Format reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Default ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*                               @arkashira

# ── Daemons (Python) — review under "agent-runtime" rubric ────────────────
/bin/axentx-*-daemon.py         @arkashira
/bin/axentx_pipeline.py         @arkashira
/bin/*.py                       @arkashira
/agents/                        @arkashira

# ── Cloudflare Worker — review under "edge-service" rubric ────────────────
/cf-worker/                     @arkashira

# ── Infra-as-code (CF/IaC/systemd) — review under "ops" rubric ────────────
/systemd/                       @arkashira
/Dockerfile                     @arkashira
/start.sh                       @arkashira
/.github/workflows/             @arkashira

# ── Docs — review under "tech-writer" rubric (lighter) ────────────────────
/docs/                          @arkashira
*.md                            @arkashira

# ── Build/config — review under "tooling" rubric ──────────────────────────
/configs/                       @arkashira
/config/                        @arkashira
/requirements.txt               @arkashira
/.devcontainer/                 @arkashira

# Notes for reviewer-daemon:
#   - Owner @arkashira is the human escalation contact (single-maintainer org)
#   - Stack-specific rubric is selected by the directory match, not the owner
#   - Add per-repo CODEOWNERS in axentx/* repos for code-specific routing
